results.deck: A Japanese development studio focused on niche titles. It is a wholly owned subsidiary of Tecmo Koei.
results.description:
Gust is most famous for it's Japanese role-playing games (J-RPG), such as the Atelier and Ar tonelico franchises. While few of its releases are big sellers, Gust remains a highly profitable company by keeping its production costs low.

After working with Gust for several years as a distributor, Tecmo Koei announced it was purchasing the studio in late 2011.
